<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/34003977-stephanie-arnold"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1408154842i/34003977._UY100_CR4,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/34003977-stephanie-arnold">Stephanie Arnold</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Yes this is a sequel to &quot;The Giver&quot; there are four in the series:<br/>1. The Giver<br/>2. Gathering Blue<br/>3. Messenger<br/>4. Son<br/><br/>If you read Messenger you will have th<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Yes this is a sequel to "The Giver" there are four in the series:<br />1. The Giver<br />2. Gathering Blue<br />3. Messenger<br />4. Son<br /><br />If you read Messenger you will have the answer to the ending of "The Giver" - did they really arrive or did they die dreaming? You will meet some old friends in #3 &amp; 4 though they will be older. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
