        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1075944783" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6538340662841179793">A quick read, that is a little confusing as it didn&apos;t seem to relate to the first book in the series.<br/><br/>Kira has just lost her mother and the only thing standing between her and the cruel women of the village. She is crippled, and in their eyes she is just another mouth to feed. One that contributes nothing. But she does have one skill, one that may save her life.<br/><br/>This world is very different from the one I entered with the first book in the series. People are dirty. They fight for food, keep their </span>
  <span id="freeText6538340662841179793" style="display:none">A quick read, that is a little confusing as it didn't seem to relate to the first book in the series.<br /><br />Kira has just lost her mother and the only thing standing between her and the cruel women of the village. She is crippled, and in their eyes she is just another mouth to feed. One that contributes nothing. But she does have one skill, one that may save her life.<br /><br />This world is very different from the one I entered with the first book in the series. People are dirty. They fight for food, keep their toddlers in pens with the fowl and live in huts. It was not what I was expecting at all.<br /><br />The treatment of kids in this book was sad for me. People in the town were selfish, and got what they wanted even at the expense of their children. The slapping and kicking was also shocking to me.<br /><br />However, I enjoyed the main character, Kira. Despite her naivety I really liked seeing through her eyes. I'm intrigued to see what happens to her, and how these worlds combine.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6538340662841179793" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
